From 49df6eb1e93cfc707aeec0697d319317f107a3c6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shankar Easwaran <seaswara@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Feb 2026 22:31:18 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] [aarch64] Fix TLS IE/GD support

This fixes an issue when object files built with TLS models
with large alignments would not produce the right values
when used with *static* links

- initial-exec
- global-dynamic

Fix description :
------------------

- AArch64IEGOT was incorrectly created with GOT::TLS_LE
- compute TLS offsets as done in static links to properly set the GOT
  slots reserved for IE/GD models
- updateTLSIEGOTOffsets() applies the correct static TLS block offset

Resolves #868

Signed-off-by: Shankar Easwaran <seaswara@qti.qualcomm.com>
(cherry picked from commit 7726200f067530e1a802041ce29f54909ef7ae07)
